Description: Sherd of pottery trefoil mouthed oinochoe neck; East Greek grey ware; thin walled; incised inscription outside.
Curator's comments: Modern incised inscription 'Diosk' in inside indicates findspot.
The vessel had been catalogued as Etruscan bucchero in the past but is more likely of East Greek production.
Bibliographic references: Etruscan Bucchero / A Catalogue of Etruscan Bucchero in the British Museum (No. 277)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GL.069)
